Here I fuse conv and bn for faster inference, and it does not work for transformers. Comment out this following line if you do not want to fuse conv&bn.
PCB_test(
  (model): ResNet(
    (conv1): Conv2d(3, 64, kernel_size=(7, 7), stride=(2, 2), padding=(3, 3))
    (bn1): Identity()
    (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
    (maxpool): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3, stride=2, padding=1, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)
    (layer1): Sequential(
      (0): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(64, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(64, 64, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(64, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (downsample): Sequential(
          (0): Conv2d(64, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
          (1): Identity()
        )
      )
      (1): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(64, 64, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(64, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (2): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(64, 64, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(64, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
    )
    (layer2): Sequential(
      (0): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(128, 128, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(2, 2), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(128, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (downsample): Sequential(
          (0): Conv2d(256, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(2, 2))
          (1): Identity()
        )
      )
      (1): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(512, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(128, 128, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(128, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (2): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(512, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(128, 128, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(128, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (3): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(512, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(128, 128, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(128, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
    )
    (layer3): Sequential(
      (0): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(2, 2), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (downsample): Sequential(
          (0): Conv2d(512, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(2, 2))
          (1): Identity()
        )
      )

        (conv1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (2): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (3): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (4): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (5): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
    )
    (layer4): Sequential(
      (0): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(1024, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (downsample): Sequential(
          (0): Conv2d(1024, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
          (1): Identity()
        )
      )
      (1): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(2048, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (2): Bottleneck(
        (conv1): Conv2d(2048, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn1): Identity()
        (conv2): Conv2d(512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (bn2): Identity()
        (conv3): Conv2d(512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        (bn3): Identity()
        (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
    )
    (avgpool): AdaptiveAvgPool2d(output_size=(1, 1))
    (fc): Linear(in_features=2048, out_features=1000, bias=True)
  )
  (avgpool): AdaptiveAvgPool2d(output_size=(6, 1))
)
